[2
Date: 31 Oct 2000 08:39:06 -0500
From: Martha Cosgriff <mcosgriff@winstar.com>
Source: Reuters and Foxnews, 31 Oct 2000 [edited
<http://www.foxnews.com/health/1031/h_rt_1031_2.sml>

French worries about BSE grew as schools in Paris banned beef from their
cafeterias and 3 cases of suspect variant Creutzfelt-Jakob Disease (nvCJD
or vCJD) surfaced in Brittany. An investigation is underway to determine if
these cases are nvCJD, which is linked to BSE.
Schools in 4 of the city's 20 districts have stopped serving beef until
further notice. It is uncertain how many other districts will follow suit.
